<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,476,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,490,1608,1634]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This species is known from three locations in the Serra do Cachimbo. In 
<collectingRegion box="[1336,1447,1608,1634]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Pará state</collectingRegion>
, it was found in anthropogenic area and Open ombrofilous forest, in humid soil near streams.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,476,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,1678,1704]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[465,780,1678,1704]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboensis">
<emphasis box="[465,780,1678,1704]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Merostachys cachimboensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from three populations registered in the Serra do Cachimbo, along the BR-163 highway. The extent of occurrence (EOO) is 
<quantity box="[997,1134,1713,1740]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.12172" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" unit="km" value="212.172">212.172 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1133,1141,1713,1727]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">2</superScript>
and the area of occupancy (AOO) is 
<quantity box="[253,375,1749,1775]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" unit="km" value="12.0">12.000 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[375,383,1748,1762]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">2</superScript>
. According to the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (2019), the new species fits in the Endangered (EN) category, based on the EOO, AOO, number of locations and area extent and/or quality of habitat [EN B1ab(iii) + B2ab(iii)].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,1049,1854,1880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,476,2092]" box="[189,1049,1854,1880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1854,1880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The epithet refers the type-locality, in the Serra do Cachimbo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,476,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1889,1915]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[356,669,1889,1915]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboensis">
<emphasis box="[356,669,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Merostachys cachimboensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[810,958,1889,1915]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delicatula">
<emphasis box="[810,958,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">M. delicatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an Atlantic Forest species only known from its type-locality in Serra da Pedra Lascada, 
<collectingRegion box="[641,706,1925,1951]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(Northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[844,917,1925,1952]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). Along with 
<taxonomicName authority="Sendulsky (1997: 295)" authorityName="Sendulsky" authorityPageNumber="295" authorityYear="1997" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptophylla">
<emphasis box="[1076,1242,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">M. leptophylla</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sendulsky, T." pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref26362" refString="Sendulsky, T. (1997) Twelve New Species of Merostachys (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae) from Brazil. Novon 7 (3): 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391946" type="journal article" year="1997">Sendulsky (1997: 295)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(registered in 
<collectingRegion box="[353,421,1960,1986]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[434,594,1960,1986]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[651,802,1960,1986]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
states), they represent the species with the smallest culm diameter of the genus (between 0.1 and 
<quantity box="[594,676,1995,2022]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
), sharing also the narrow foliage blades (&lt;
<quantity box="[1172,1253,1995,2022]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" unit="cm" value="0.8">0.8 cm</quantity>
), a character also found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Sendulsky (1997: 287)" authorityName="Sendulsky" authorityPageNumber="287" authorityYear="1997" box="[242,649,2030,2056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argentea">
<emphasis box="[242,380,2031,2056]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">M. argentea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sendulsky, T." box="[389,649,2030,2056]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref26362" refString="Sendulsky, T. (1997) Twelve New Species of Merostachys (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae) from Brazil. Novon 7 (3): 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391946" type="journal article" year="1997">Sendulsky (1997: 287)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sendulsky (1997: 290)" authorityName="Sendulsky" authorityPageNumber="290" authorityYear="1997" box="[708,1120,2030,2056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifurcata">
<emphasis box="[708,849,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="112">M. bifurcata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sendulsky, T." box="[858,1120,2030,2056]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref26362" refString="Sendulsky, T. (1997) Twelve New Species of Merostachys (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae) from Brazil. Novon 7 (3): 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391946" type="journal article" year="1997">Sendulsky (1997: 290)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both Atlantic Forest species (
<bibRefCitation author="Sendulsky, T." box="[144,329,2065,2092]" pageId="13" pageNumber="112" pagination="285 - 307" refId="ref26362" refString="Sendulsky, T. (1997) Twelve New Species of Merostachys (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae) from Brazil. Novon 7 (3): 285 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3391946" type="journal article" year="1997">Sendulsky 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="14" pageNumber="113" startId="14.[136,229,1821,1843]" targetBox="[161,1409,198,1764]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1821,1951]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,255,1821,1843]" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
Illustration of 
<taxonomicName authority=": A. Rhizomes. B. Bud" box="[401,892,1821,1843]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboensis">
<emphasis box="[401,671,1821,1842]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Merostachys cachimboensis</emphasis>
: A. Rhizomes. B. Bud
</taxonomicName>
frontal view. C. Bud lateral view. D. Terminal culm with culm leaves. E. Culm leaf sheath, abaxial view. F. Culm leaf fimbriae. G. Culm leaf blade. H. Internode with branch complement and foliage leaf complement. I. Foliage leaf fimbriae. J. Foliage leaf blade detail of the adaxial surface with prominent nerves. Drawn by R.B.Lopes-Neto, based on the holotype [
<emphasis box="[529,736,1929,1951]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Lopes-Neto et al. 693</emphasis>
(MG)].
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1452,158,401]" pageId="15" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicName box="[189,507,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboensis">
<emphasis box="[189,507,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="114">Merostachys cachimboensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[641,794,158,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delicatula">
<emphasis box="[641,794,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="114">M. delicatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the habit initially erect then arching and clambering surrounding the vegetation, culms &lt;
<quantity box="[561,639,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter, glabrous to scabrous toward the apex, foliage leaf sheath glabrous, fimbriae yellow-white, straight to sinuous at the apex, blades linear-lanceolate to lanceolate, base rounded and apex attenuate. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[484,688,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="15" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cachimboensis">
<emphasis box="[484,688,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="114">M. cachimboensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the absence of an infranodal band of trichomes, branch complement with 20–55 branches, foliage leaf blades with the L:W ratio = 12.6–21.6, strongly reflexed and adaxially with 2–3 prominent and scabrous lateral nerves on one side, when 3, the lateral ones more prominent than the middle one (
<tableCitation box="[191,279,374,400]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="15.[136,224,448,472]" captionText="TABLE 2. Morphological comparison between Merostachys cachimboensis and M. delicatula." pageId="15" pageNumber="114">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
